Location: Kilsyth, Yarra Valley & High Country VIC (Hybrid)
Ad Text:
Work at the forefront of the AI revolution.  Join AFL and be part of our data centre growth journey!  




About AFL    

At AFL, we’re enabling the AI era and shaping the future of connectivity. We connect customers worldwide with innovative technologies, quality products, and exceptional service. Serving Enterprise, Industrial, Service Provider, and Hyperscale markets, we deliver end-to-end fibre connectivity solutions backed by world-class expertise.    

We’re a customer-first, community-centred organisation... and we’re growing fast.  




The Opportunity  

Australia & New Zealand’s data centre industry is booming, and AFL is expanding to meet this demand. It’s an exciting time to join us as we scale and innovate!  

We’re seeking Expressions of Interest across multiple disciplines to help our customers deploy at speed and shape critical infrastructure for the digital future.  

Our dedicated Data Centre Services team are expanding and seeking expressions of interest from dynamic, customer-focussed individuals to help support critical and high-value data centre deployments and structured cabling projects.  

In this impactful role, you will:  

Partner with customers to translate their needs into integrated AFL solutions, including developing reference architectures, network schematics and BOMs, and advising on performance, density, scalability and deployment best practice; 

Provide technical support across the project lifecycle including pre‑sales consulting, solution integration, training and ongoing technical oversight to ensure successful delivery; 

Provide remote or hands on on‑site expertise, including splicing, inspection, testing and commissioning, while troubleshooting and optimising installations to maintain high‑quality outcomes; and 

Elevate our solutions through continuous improvement, capturing Voice‑of‑Customer insights and site learnings to refine AFL’s products, deployment standards and customer experience. 




What You’ll Bring  

Relevant experience in data centre operations, structured cabling, or telecommunications, ideally with a relevant engineering qualification and white card.  

Highly analytical and proficient in technical concepts and products 

Customer centric with clear and confident internal and external communication skills, and a passion for solving customer problems under pressure  

Agile, collaborative, and comfortable working at pace with accountability  
  

If this opportunity excites you but you don’t meet every requirement, we’d still love to hear from you.   




Why AFL    

Join a global leader in fibre optics and make an impact on essential infrastructure. At AFL, you’ll enjoy:    

Working at the cutting edge of technology, with a supportive team and culture  

Highly competitive remuneration   

Genuine career pathways, global exposure and extensive learning & development    

Benefits including hybrid and flexible work options, birthday leave, novated leasing, top-up parental leave, EAP, community outreach, onsite parking, and more  




Ready to grow with us?    

Don’t miss the chance to be part of our growth story. Express your interest today and help shape the future of data centre connectivity!

About Us.

Oolio/Swiftpos is an Australian owned Point of Sale and payments company that creates bespoke solutions for the Hospitality and Retail industries. We have offices across Australia, the UK and the US and provide a full suite of management systems, to deliver excellent governance and member engagement to thousands of clients worldwide. Our fully integrated business solutions are well known within the stadia space and cater specifically to the sports, leisure, and the food and beverage sectors. For the past thirty years our management systems have underpinned some of the biggest clubs and venues in Australia and around the world. 

We are looking for an experienced AI Developer to join our team and help build cutting-edge image recognition solutions for Point of Sale (POS) environments. Your work will focus on enabling real-time item detection and classification using advanced computer vision models integrated into POS systems. 

Your Key Responsibilities will be to;

Design, train, and optimize object detection models for retail environments. 

Implement and deploy lightweight AI models for edge devices and web-based applications. 

Integrate AI pipelines with POS systems for seamless user experience. 

Collaborate with product and engineering teams to ensure scalability and performance. 

In this role you will be working alongside a diverse team of developers on new versions of our customized and bespoke products. You will have the opportunity to work across various products with the latest tools, techniques and languages such as;

Languages & Frameworks: C#, SQL Server, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (Libraries/Frameworks), ASP.NET MVC, Vue.js.

Platforms: Progressive Web Apps.

Tools: Git (Bitbucket), AWS, TeamCity, Octopus. 

Methodologies: Agile (Scrum, Kanban).

We are looking for a candidate with;

Strong experience in AI/Computer Vision, specifically object detection. 

Hands-on expertise with YOLOv8 (nano variant preferred) for lightweight deployments or equivalent 

Proficiency in ONNX Runtime Web for browser-based inference.  

Solid understanding of model optimization techniques (quantization, pruning).  

Familiarity with JavaScript/TypeScript and Web Assembly for client-side AI execution.  

Experience building edge services in Go, .NET, or C++ for low-latency, real-time systems.

Python experience for training, fine-tuning, and exporting YOLO models prior to deployment.

Infrastructure and deployment experience, particularly with Kubernetes, to support distributed edge services, reliable rollouts, and lifecycle management.

Experience deploying AI models in real-time environments with performance constraints. 

Knowledge of current and emerging web technologies 

Full working rights in Australia.

Why Join Oolio? 

You’ll work closely with a visionary C.T.O and Developers in a high-performance, collaborative team. We offer opportunities to: 

Contribute to critical software solutions 

Work with the latest tools and technologies 

To grow your career and skills across diverse products 

The opportunity to work a hybrid week (3 days in office, 2 days remote)

If this role is of interest to you, please apply via the Seek link with a current resume.
